description:
&lt;p&gt;From a friendly face to providing professional support, as a Family Therapist, you are the reason why lives change for the better.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working at Brighton &amp; Hove Clinic, you will join the multidisciplinary team that provides CAMHS Tier 4 service for young people aged 12 - 18 years with a prime diagnosis of eating disorders and who may have other metals health conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work 37.5 hours a week which includes one day over the weekend and a late session to 20:00 a month. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the Therapy Lead, you will provide specialist systemic psychotherapy assessments and interventions, offer psychotherapy perspective and advice, and will be the care coordinator for one or more young people.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Family Therapist, you will have experience and knowledge in carrying a service users caseload, including assessing service users with complex needs, supporting families and care plans and designing and delivering specialist psychological treatment within CAMHS Eating Disorder services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As a Family Therapist, you will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete all recording and reporting tasks associated with clinical work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to training and supervision of ward staff as provided by the psychological therapies team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To continually monitor risk of all service users for whom there is direct contact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare clinical; reports as required, e.g. assessment reports, discharge summaries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will get&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Annual salary of £45,000 - £50,000&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The equivalent of 33 days annual leave – plus your birthday off!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free meals &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wellbeing support and activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Career development and training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pension contribution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Life Assurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enhanced Maternity Package&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is also a range of other benefits including retail discounts and special offers, car leasing without a credit check, holiday financing and much more.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About your next employer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working for an established, stable and agile company with a unique approach to the delivery of care. With a network of over 70 services across England and Wales, providing four services including: Mental Health, Neurological, Learning Disabilities &amp; Autism, Children &amp; Education, there is an opportunity for you to grow and move with Elysium.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Elysium Healthcare follows safer recruitment of staff for all appointments. It is a requirement that all staff understand it is each person’s individual responsibility and are committed to promoting and safeguarding the welfare of service users. Candidates will be subject to an Enhanced DBS disclosure.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
